TITLE: Border Patrol opens gate locked by Texas National Guard to allow illegal immigrants to enter
SUMMARY: Border Patrol agents unlocked a gate that had been locked by Texas National Guard. The move allowed a number of illegal immigrants to enter and be processed.

TITLE: FBI probes Atlanta Black extremist group allegedly arming homeless men, infiltrating protests
SUMMARY: The FBI is reportedly investigating the Black Hammer Party for kidnapping, human trafficking, narcotics and other charges carried out by the armed extremist group of homeless Black men.

TITLE: US, allies send thousands of soldiers for Indo-Pacific military drills as China continues Taiwan aggression
SUMMARY: The United States and allies sent thousands of soldiers to Indonesia for military drills--the largest of such exercises since they began in 2009--as China threatens Taiwan.

TITLE: McCarthy aide reacts to Liz Cheney attack with 'ironic' Dick Cheney quote
SUMMARY: House Republican Leader Kevin McCarthy's office defended the representative's leadership after outgoing Wyoming Rep. Liz Cheney said McCarthy was unfit for the role.

TITLE: Strategists suggest it's 'highly doubtful' Liz Cheney could win the White House in 2024
SUMMARY: Political strategist are sounding off on whether they believe Rep. Liz Cheney has a shot at a successful run for president in 2024 over former President Donald Trump.

TITLE: McConnell quiet on Cheney primary loss after previously expressing support for congresswoman
SUMMARY: The top two Senate Republicans as of Wednesday afternoon did not comment on Rep. Liz Cheney losing her Wyoming primary race to challenger Harriet Hageman.

TITLE: Planned Parenthood to spend historic $50 million on midterm elections, pro-life group calls action 'desperate'
SUMMARY: Planned Parenthood announces plans to spend $50 million on this years midterm elections, in an effort to combat the Supreme Court's June ruling to overturn Roe v. Wade.

TITLE: Murkowski and Trump-backed Tshibaka advance to Alaska general election for Senate
SUMMARY: Sen. Lisa Murkowski and Kelly Tshibaka are among the four candidates who will advance to the November general election in the race to represent Alaska in the Senate.

TITLE: GOP worried Big Tech, Disney creating hostile work environment for pregnant women with abortion emphasis
SUMMARY: A top House Oversight Republican is concerned the emphasis on abortion access by technology companies is creating a hostile work environment for pregnant women.

TITLE: Republicans probing if Biden plans to use Amtrak to transport illegal aliens for immigration processing
SUMMARY: House Republican are concerned the Biden administration is planning to use Amtrak to transport illegal aliens from the U.S.-Mexico border for immigration processing.

TITLE: Oregon GOP gubernatorial nominee Christine Drazan announces massive seven-figure ad buy in push to flip state
SUMMARY: Oregon GOP gubernatorial hopeful Christine Drazan announced Wednesday a seven-figure ad buy aimed at addressing quality of life issues in the state.

TITLE: Florida prosecutor Andrew Warren sues Gov. Ron DeSantis over suspension
SUMMARY: Florida prosecutor Andrew Warren filed a lawuit against Gov. Ron DeSantis, seeking reinstatement after DeSantis suspended him for refusing to prosecute certain offenses.

TITLE: Ted Cruz stopping in Iowa on Thursday to support Chuck Grassley’s Senate re-election bid
SUMMARY: Conservative firebrand Sen. Ted Cruz will stop in Iowa on Thursday, on a 2022 mission that’s also sure to spark more speculation about a potential 2024 White House run

TITLE: Texas border town mayor says 'broken' immigration system can be solved if Dems, GOP cooperate
SUMMARY: The massive influx of illegal immigrants at the southern border can be solved through a bipartisan, national approach, a Texas border town mayor told Fox News.

TITLE: Migrant encounters at southern border exceed 2 million so far in FY 22, as Biden-era crisis continues
SUMMARY: There have been more than two million migrant encounters so far this fiscal year, according to sources who spoke to Fox News, hitting a new record for encounters.

TITLE: Rudy Giuliani arrives at Georgia courthouse for ordered testimony in Trump criminal probe
SUMMARY: Former Trump attorney Rudy Giuliani arrived at an Atlanta, Georgia, courthouse on Wednesday for court-ordered testimony in Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis’ criminal probe.

TITLE: After landslide primary defeat, Liz Cheney announces new anti-Trump group, says she's 'thinking about' WH bid
SUMMARY: Rep. Liz Cheney, fresh off a staggering primary defeat to a challenger backed by former President Donald Trump, said her main goal is keep Trump out of the White House.

TITLE: Elon Musk spoke at GOP leader Kevin McCarthy's Wyoming retreat on same day Liz Cheney lost primary
SUMMARY: Elon Musk attended a fundraiser retreat in Wyoming that was hosted by GOP leader Kevin McCarthy on the same day Wyoming Rep. Liz Cheney lost her Republican primary election.

TITLE: Trump blasts Liz Cheney after primary loss to Harriet Hagerman: 'She can finally disappear'
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump released a statement condemning Wyoming Rep. Liz Cheney following her Republican primary loss to his endorsed candidate Harriet Hageman.

TITLE: Sen. Tom Cotton’s 2022 mission to ‘put the brakes’ on Biden’s agenda may be prelude for potential 2024 run
SUMMARY: Sen. Tom Cotton's travels across the country this year to help 2022 Republicans may set him up for 2024 GOP White House run of his own
